          <p>Among many such studies, one by Khan et al. in the American Accounting Association Review shows that funds which implemented E.S.G. strategies in the '90s have clearly outperformed those that have not.<sup><a href="#4">4</a></sup> </p>
          <p> In addition to demonstrable financial incentives, the change is being driven by investor demands. At a 2017 interview</p>
